# Styling & UI Guidelines

## Design System Reference

See `DESIGN.md` at the repo root for the canonical UI specification: colors (indigo primary `#6366F1`), typography (General Sans / DM Sans / JetBrains Mono), elevation, component variants, spacing (4px base), border radii, and do's/don'ts. Consult it before introducing UI changes or new components.

## Configured Tokens â€” Use These, Not Hardcoded Utilities

```typescript
// âś… GOOD â€” semantic tokens
<div className="bg-surface text-foreground border border-border rounded-card shadow-card-hover">
<button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary-hover hover:shadow-primary-glow">
<span className="text-text-secondary text-small">Metadata</span>
<h1 className="font-display text-section tracking-heading-tight">TĂ­tulo</h1>
<Chip className="bg-destructive/10 text-destructive rounded-chip">Vencido</Chip>

// âťŚ BAD â€” hardcoded colors that bypass the design system
<div className="bg-white text-gray-900 border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
<button className="bg-indigo-600 text-white hover:bg-indigo-700">
<span className="text-gray-500 text-sm">Metadata</span>
<h1 className="text-3xl font-bold">TĂ­tulo</h1>
<span className="text-red-500">Vencido</span>
```

**Color tokens**: `background` / `surface` / `foreground` / `text-secondary` / `muted-foreground` / `primary` (+ `primary-hover`) / `secondary` / `success` / `warning` / `destructive` / `border`. Always pair `bg-X` with `text-X-foreground`.

**Font families**: `font-display` (General Sans, headings only) Â· `font-sans` (DM Sans, default body) Â· `font-mono` (JetBrains Mono, code/numbers).

**Type scale**: `text-overline` Â· `text-caption` Â· `text-small` Â· `text-body` Â· `text-subhead` Â· `text-section` Â· `text-headline` Â· `text-display`.

**Radius**: `rounded-chip` (4px) Â· `rounded-md`/`rounded-lg` (6px) Â· `rounded-panel` (8px) Â· `rounded-card` (12px) Â· `rounded-full`.

**Shadows**: `shadow-card-hover` Â· `shadow-primary-glow` Â· `shadow-focus-ring`.

## Tailwind CSS Patterns

```typescript
// âś… GOOD - Use utility classes
<div className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 rounded-lg">

// âś… GOOD - Use cn() for conditional classes
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
<div className={cn(
  "rounded-lg p-4",
  isActive && "bg-green-100",
  isDue && "bg-red-100"
)}>

// âťŚ BAD - Avoid custom CSS when possible
<div style={{ display: "flex", padding: "16px" }}>
```

## shadcn/ui Components

```typescript
// âś… GOOD - Import from @/components/ui
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Dialog } from "@/components/ui/dialog";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";

// âś… GOOD - Use shadcn/ui over custom implementations
<Button variant="destructive" size="sm">
  Eliminar
</Button>
```

